    "The City of Dakar will implement its Territorial Climate Energy Plan (PCET) to set targets to reduce GHG emissions and reduce its vulnerability to climate change.": 0,
    "Dakar will undertake a participatory and inclusive approach by mobilizing all stakeholders to achieve its climate plan objectives.": 0,
    "The City of Dakar will strengthen its climate governance by diagnosing its GHG emissions and vulnerability and integrating renewables, energy savings in municipal buildings and public lighting, soft transport modes, circular economy, and green spaces into municipal policy.": 0,
    "By 2050, Dakar aims to achieve a 54% reduction in GHG emissions, a 75% reduction in the energy bill of the City’s built heritage, and at least a 65% share of renewable energy in the energy mix.": 0,
    "Dakar will pursue adaptation objectives including strengthening climate/coastal/urban pollution data networks; reducing vulnerable populations through awareness; reducing heatwave vulnerability; increasing protection initiatives; reducing air pollutants by 2030; increasing urban green spaces by 150 ha by 2030; expanding ecological urban agriculture by 2030; and increasing climate-resilient infrastructure.": 0,
    "Dakar will implement energy efficiency actions in municipal buildings and public lighting, avoiding 441.39 tCO2eq (81% below BAU) in audited buildings and achieving 57% GHG reduction potential in public lighting, with an estimated overall 62% reduction (about 2,823 tCO2eq/year avoided) if implemented across the city’s heritage.": 0,
    "The City of Dakar will establish an energy and ecological transition programme that prioritizes energy efficiency, including measures such as improved pricing/power factor, LED lighting and controls, efficient air conditioning, equipment changes, pump performance improvements, and integration of renewables (mini solar plants and solar water heaters), achieving up to 51% savings on subscribed electricity and 81% on energy consumption.": 0,
